one;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4533,\"repo\":\"owncast/owncast\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Selfhosted video streaming plattform (<a href=\"https://owncast.online/\">https://owncast.online/</a>)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T17:29:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/statistical-machine-translation/94EADF9F680558E13BE759997553CDE5#fndtn-information\">Statistical Machine Translation</a> - Establishes background in NLP and statistics, then develops the basics through to current research. By the end readers can build their own translation systems. The author is <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philipp_Koehn\">Philipp Koehn</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T17:18:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/neural-machine-translation/7AAA628F88ADD64124EA008C425C0197#fndtn-information\">Neural Machine Translation</a> - This introduction to machine translation starts from the basics of neural network methods and reaches the state of the art, while giving historical, linguistic, and applied context. Code examples in Python give a hands-on blueprint for implementation. The author is still Philipp Koehn.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T17:18:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Translation-advanced-resource-Routledge-Linguistics-ebook/dp/B07NPV8DSC/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_product_top?ie=UTF8\">Translation: An advanced resource book for students</a> - Introduces the theory and practice of translation from a variety of linguistic and cultural angles. The authors are <a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=IVydQ-4AAAAJ&#x26;hl=en\">Basil Hatim</a> and <a href=\"https://ahc.leeds.ac.uk/languages/staff/1006/professor-jeremy-munday\">Jeremy Munday</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T17:18:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"michelpereira/awesome-games-of-coding","categoryHTML":"<h2>Language Independent</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codecombat.com\">CodeCombat</a> - Choose your hero and code your way through the ogre patrols, lava pits, and laser beams of Kithgard Dungeon. Level up, earn gems, and loot magic items to unlock new programming powers. Join millions of players and go from a total beginner to writing advanced multiplayer AI in Python, JavaScript, CoffeeScript, or Lua in this open-source programming game.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T14:38:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"michelpereira/awesome-games-of-coding","categoryHTML":"<h2>JavaScript</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jsfight.club\">JavaScript Fight Club</a> - The Red King and the Blue King are at war! Your JavaScript skills are needed to determine the victor: Can you code an effective AI for honor and glory?</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T14:38:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"michelpereira/awesome-games-of-coding","categoryHTML":"<h2>JavaScript</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://play.elevatorsaga.com\">Elevator Saga</a> - Write JavaScript directly in the browser to program an elevator, such that it reaches its efficiency goals. Start with simple \"getting started\" scripts, and ramp up to much more complex situations with many floors and multiple elevators.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T14:38:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"michelpereira/awesome-games-of-coding","categoryHTML":"<h2>JavaScript</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://alexnisnevich.github.io/untrusted\">Untrusted</a> - The game presents you with a roguelike-like playing environment and a console window with the JavaScript code generating each level. As loaded, each level is unbeatable, and most of the JavaScript is blocked from editing. The challenge is to open a path to the next level using only the limited tools left open to you.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T14:38:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"iamericfletcher/awesome-r-learning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://martinctc.github.io/blog/\">Musings on R</a> - A blog on all things R and Data Science by Martin Chan. Topics covered include comparing dplyr and data.table, Shiny apps, ggplot, data cleaning, using RStudio, interviews with other R users/data scientists, and web scraping.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T13:41:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"troxler/awesome-css-frameworks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Base / Reset / Normalize</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hankchizljaw/modern-css-reset\"><strong>modern-css-reset</strong></a> - Tiny little reset that you can use as the basis of your CSS projects.<br>\n<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/stars/hankchizljaw/modern-css-reset.svg?style=social&#x26;label=Star\" alt=\"\">\n<a href=\"https://github.com/hankchizljaw/modern-css-reset\">Repo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/hankchizljaw/modern-css-reset\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1780,\"repo\":\"hankchizljaw/modern-css-reset\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->\n| #CSS</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T12:04:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://guides.rubyonrails.org/i18n.html\">Ruby I18n</a> - Rails internationalization (i18n) API.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:08:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://quasar.dev/options/app-internationalization\">Quasar I18n</a> - App internationalization (i18n) in Quasar framework.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:08:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/754520/what-is-the-actual-differences-between-i18n-l10n-g11n-and-specifically-what-does\">Stack Overflow Q&#x26;A-2</a> - What is the actual differences between i18n/l10n/g11n and specifically what does each mean for development?</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:07:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/maximbilan/SwiftGoogleTranslate\">SwiftGoogleTranslate</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/maximbilan/SwiftGoogleTranslate\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">51</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":51,\"repo\":\"maximbilan/SwiftGoogleTranslate\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A framework to use cloud translation API by Google in Swift.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:04:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://crowdsource.google.com/\">Google Crowdsource</a> - Crowdsourcing platform developed by Google intended to improve a host of Google services through the user-facing training of different algorithms (with translation and translation validation section).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:04:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://lingocode.com/translation-blog/\">The Translator's Teacup</a> - Contains good tips for beginner translators.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:03:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://foxdocs.biz/BetweenTranslations/\">Between Translations</a> - Run by Jayne Fox, a German into English translator. It talks about continuing professional development (CPD) for translators and the use of technology (especially CAT tools/TEnTs) to support their work.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:03:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/machinetranslation\">Machine Translation</a> - Explains the basic principles of translation algoritms. It is provided by the Karlsruhe Institute of Technology (Germany).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T11:03:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/python-i18n/\">Python-i18n</a> - Python internationalization (i18n) package.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T10:51:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/debian-reference/ch08.en.html\">Debian manuals</a> - Chapter 8: i18n and l10n.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T10:51:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developer.chrome.com/webstore/i18n\">Developer Chrome i18n</a> - Internationalizing your app.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T10:51:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://lx.berkeley.edu/sites/default/files/berkeleylinguisticsdeptg11ncldr.pdf\">Software Globalization, Berkeley.edu - slides</a> - \"Software globalization and adding languages on computers and mobile devices\" by Craig Cummings (slides).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T10:51:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-i18n\">W3C</a> - Localization vs. internationalization.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T10:51:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer-assisted_translation\">Computer-assisted translation</a> - CAT (computer-aided translation) tools are typically understood to mean programs that specifically facilitate the actual translation process. This article describe: translation memory software, language search-engine software, terminology management software, alignment software, interactive machine translation, augmented translation.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T10:51:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.edx.org/professional-certificate/uwashingtonx-internationalization-and-localization\">UWashingtonX's I18n and l10n</a> - A collection of 3 courses of internationalization and internationalization for digital products provided by the University of Washington.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T10:51:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome","categoryHTML":"<h2>Work</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/j0hnm4r5/awesome-creative-technology#readme\">Creative Technology</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/j0hnm4r5/awesome-creative-technology#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">54</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":54,\"repo\":\"j0hnm4r5/awesome-creative-technology\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Businesses &#x26; groups that specialize in combining computing, design, art, and user experience.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-12-20T09:54:28.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1608422400000,"to":1608508799999,"previousId":"2020-12-21","nextId":"2020-12-19","nextName":"Dec 19th, 2020","previousName":"Dec 21st, 2020"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","4035379035"]}